Stash Backup Client passes the password in {{backup-config.properties}} as a string literal, not a string collection/array, so any password or username with a special character may have unintended issues. The current version of the backup script can’t handle normal special, reserved characters “\”, “””, “;” etc. This appears to be because the existing jar doesn’t do any string conversion or sanitization and the documentation makes no mention of this.

Stash Backup Client will error with:


{code:java}
2015-06-18 10:42:39,758 ERROR [main] c.a.s.i.backup.client.BackupMain A backup could not be created. Reason: The Stash version could not be verified; the server returned 401 Unauthorized. Backup/restore is only supported by Stash 2.7.0 and later.
{code}

